s patient experiences, clinician workflows, and internal toolsΓÇöwhile also helping define how we build (development practices, quality bar, and technical defaults). This role is an AI-forward role where youΓÇÖll have real latitude to experiment with modern AI tooling to increase our engineering velocity, and to identify, prototype, and ship AI-powered product capabilities where they meaningfully improve outcomes and patient experience.\n\nOur Stack\nWeb: Next.js (React), TypeScript, Modern CSS\n\nBackend: Node.js / Next API Routes\n\nData: PostgreSQL, Redis\n\nTesting: Vitest, React Testing Library, Playwright, Github Actions\n\nInfrastructure: Aptible (Experience with AWS or GCP is a plus)\n\nWhat YouΓÇÖll Do\nOwn Features End-to-End: Take a feature from a loosely defined problem or ambiguous "what if..." through requirements, development, and deliveryΓÇöcollaborating directly with product and clinical stakeholders to deliver high impact results.\n\nBuild Across the Stack: Develop features for our patient-facing apps, pediatrician dashboards, and internal clinical toolsΓÇöworking across the frontend, backend, and mobile.\n\nUse AI to Move Faster: Experiment with the latest AI tooling, share what you learn and help raise the bar for how we all work.\n\nLead Technical Decisions: Help define our engineering processesΓÇöCI/CD improvements, code quality, testing strategy, API & database design.\n\nMove Fast, Stay Secure: Ship high-velocity code while maintaining the rigorous security standards required for HIPAA-compliant healthcare.\n\nWho You Are\n3-5 Years Experience: You're proficient in our stack: Next.js, TypeScript, and SQL. You have depth in at least one area (frontend, backend, or mobile) and genuine interest in learning the others as needed\n\nA Problem-Solver at Heart: YouΓÇÖre comfortable with ambiguity, can turn sparse requirements into a plan, and drive work from ΓÇ£what do we need?ΓÇ¥ to shipped outcomes with minimal oversight.\n\nAI-Native: AI-Native: You already use AI to speed up your workflow and you're genuinely excited to push the boundaries of what's possible. You'll help the team experiment and adopt new tools alongside you.\n\nCollaborative Self-Starter: You thrive in a remote environment where communication is proactive and the mission is the North Star.\n\nRegulated Industry Veteran: Bonus if you have worked in HealthTech, FinTech, or similar spaces. Able to understand that security and privacy aren't "features"ΓÇöthey are the foundation.\n\nWhat We Offer\nMeaningful Impact: Your code will literally change the lives of children and parents navigating chronic conditions.\n\nGrowth & Equity: Competitive salary plus an equity stake in a high-growth, venture-backed startup.\n\nFlexible Remote Culture: Work from anywhere in the US. (Optional monthly meetups for SF Bay Area locals).\n\nFull Benefits: Medical, Dental, Vision, 401k, and flexible PTO.\n\nApply for this Job\nThis site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply.\n\nPowered by \nPrivacy PolicySecurityVulnerability Disclosure\n\n	1
