alued.ΓÇ» \nΓÇ» \nBoostlingo is extremely honored to have been recognized as one of Inc. Magazine's Best Workplaces for the last three consecutive years (2022-2025). This esteemed recognition reflects the dedication that our incredible team has towards embodying our Core Values every day and we couldnΓÇÖt be prouder of this team! \n\n \n\n \n\nABOUT THE ROLE  \nBoostlingo is looking for a Senior Full Stack Developer to join our Enterprise Development Team. This team is responsible for building and maintaining systems that integrate BoostlingoΓÇÖs platform with enterprise healthcare systems and EHRs. \n\nThis is a full stack role first. EHR and healthcare domain experience is a strong plus, but not a hard requirement. \n\nAs a senior individual contributor, you will: \n\nOwn systems end-to-end \nInfluence architecture and technical direction \nWork on complex integrations with enterprise partners \nRaise the bar for quality, reliability, and maintainability \nThis is not a ΓÇ£ticket factoryΓÇ¥ role. You will be expected to think in systems, understand tradeoffs, and help the team scale responsibly.\n\n \n\n  \n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO: \nDesign, build, and maintain full stack web applications and services supporting enterprise and healthcare integrations \nDevelop and maintain backend services and APIs that integrate with internal systems and external EHR platforms \nBuild scalable, secure, multi-tenant services used by healthcare and enterprise customers \nCollaborate with product, platform, and operations teams on system design and architecture \nBuild and maintain public and internal APIs used by web, mobile, IVR, and partner systems \nImprove system reliability, performance, and observability \nWrite and maintain automated tests (unit, integration, and end-to-end where appropriate) \nHelp modernize legacy systems while maintaining uptime and stability \nParticipate in on-call rotation and production incident response when required \nMentor engineers through code reviews,