ering\nZipRecruiter.org\nZipRecruiter UK\nLogos provided by Clearbit\nYour privacy is our priority. Learn more: Your Privacy Choices\n\nPrivacy Policy\nCalifornia Privacy Notice\nTerms of Use\nCookie Policy\nAttribution Notices\nCorporate Responsibility\nSecurity and Compliance\nZipRecruiter, Inc. ┬⌐ 2026 All Rights Reserved Worldwide\n\n\n\n\nBack to Home\nSr. Software Engineer - AI-Driven Front-end Development\nMagieva\nLos Angeles, CA ΓÇó Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\n$110K - $180K/yr\n\nFull-time\n\nMedical, Dental, Vision, Life, Retirement, PTO\n\nPosted 24 days ago\n\nBe Seen First\n\nAfter you apply to this job, you can share why youΓÇÖre interested to jump to the top of the candidate list.\n\nJob description\nThis is not a traditional coding role. You will orchestrate AI tools like Claude Code to build, ship, and scale production features across a multi-service platform. Your success depends on directing AI agents to deliver pixel-perfect UIs, robust backend integrations, and enterprise-grade code quality.\n\nStack: Claude Code, Docker, Next.js, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Go, PostgreSQL, Redis, WebSockets\n\n---\n\nWhat You'll Do\n- Direct AI agents to build modern web UIs: multi-panel layouts, dashboards, data tables, forms, modals, and search interfaces\n- Guide agents to implement polish: animations, transitions, loading states, micro-interactions, and smooth user experiences\n- Translate Figma designs into prompts that produce production-ready, responsive components\n- Audit agent output for design consistency: alignment, spacing, responsive breakpoints, and pixel-perfect implementation\n- Orchestrate component library usage and ensure consistent design system application\n- Direct agents to integrate frontend with Go microservices (REST APIs + WebSockets for real-time features)\n- Guide agents through complex features: schema migrations, event-driven patterns, multi-database operations\n- Ensure proper error handling, loading states, optimistic updates, and keyboard shortcuts\n- Audit cross-service integrations for security, performance, and multi-tenancy requirements\n- Manage parallel agent workflows to maximize velocity while maintaining code quality\n- Decompose complex features into effective prompts that produce tested, documented code\n- Iterate on agent output to fix UI bugs: z-index issues, layout shifts, animation glitches\n- Optimize agent-generated code for performance and enterprise SaaS standards\n\n---\n\nMust-Haves\n- Deep experience using Claude Code, Cursor, or Copilot to drive production development\n- Proven ability to prompt AI agents for complex features while maintaining quality standards\n- Strong React/Next.js + TypeScript production experience to effectively audit agent output\n- Solid Go backend experience to review microservice patterns and API integrations\n- Expert-level understanding of component libraries, CSS architecture, and responsive design\n- Animation expertise: CSS transitions, Framer Motion, Tailwind animations\n- "Pixel-perfect" eye for design inconsistencies, alignment issues, and visual bugs\n- Strong design sense to bridge Figma mockups and production implementation\n- Performance optimization mindset: lazy loading, code splitting, query optimization\n- Understanding of accessibility, cross-browser compatibility, and edge cases\n- Experience with multi-tenancy, data isolation, and security best practices\n- Familiarity with testing culture, documentation standards, and CI/CD workflows\n- Force multiplier mentality: ships full features independently via AI orchestration\n- Self-directed problem-solving and architectural decision-making\n- Thrives with minimal oversight while maintaining high quality standards\n\n---\n\nWhat Success Looks Like\nYou direct AI agents like a sr. engineer leads a development team. You architect solutions, write effective prompts, and audit output with a critical eye. You catch what agents miss: misaligned pixels, performance bottlenecks, security gaps, UX friction.\nYou ship features that feel hand-crafted, users can't tell it was AI-generated. From Figma to production, you orchestrate every detail: smooth animations, error handling, loading states, edge cases.\nYou're equally comfortable directing agents to build a polished dashboard UI as guiding them through a complex database migration. You understand the full stack deeply enough to spot issues at any layer.\nYou thrive in a fast-paced environment where AI tools are your leverage. You're not waiting for perfect requirements, you ask questions, propose solutions, iterate quickly, and ship continuously.\n\n---\n\nThis role is for someone who sees AI coding tools as the future of software development and wants to be at the forefront of this transformation.\n\n\nReport	3
