178	Alvys	Senior Product Engineer	t	2026-03-12 08:12:24.154	Senior Software Engineer\nUnited States (Remote)\nAbout the Role\n\nAlvys is building the operating system for modern freight with a multi-tenant SaaS platform that streamlines day-to-day transportation operations. As a Senior Product Engineer, you will be a senior individual contributor who owns meaningful product areas end-to-end: shaping what we build, how we build it, and whether it worked for customers.\n\nThis role is designed for engineers who want to sit at the intersection of engineering execution, product judgment, and operational ownership, and who are excited to build with AI as a first-class part of the workflow.\n\nWe are moving quickly toward an AI-first operating model across the company. On the engineering side, we have shifted from a traditional model with many handoffs (PRDs ΓåÆ designs ΓåÆ engineering ΓåÆ QA) to a product engineering model where engineers are accountable for outcomes and leverage AI to accelerate delivery.\n\nAI is a core part of how we build\n\nWe are building Alvys with AI as a first-class part of the workflow. As a Senior Product Engineer, you will use AI to move faster while keeping quality high, and you will still be accountable for outcomes.\n\nYou will be expected to be fluent in modern AI tooling and patterns, including:\n\nUsing AI tools to accelerate implementation, debugging, and test generation.\nReviewing and hardening AI-generated code with strong engineering judgment.\nIterating quickly with customer feedback and production signal.\nContributing to evolving team practices as the AI toolchain changes.\nIn this role, ΓÇ£seniorΓÇ¥ is measured by impact. That means owning customer and business outcomes, influencing product direction through strong problem framing and tradeoffs, and shipping and operating production systems with a reliability mindset.\n\nIndustry Insight\n\nTransportation logistics is massive, fragmented, and still underserved by modern software. The work is complex, the stakes are high, and the opportunity is huge: improving how freight moves impacts costs, service levels, and reliability across the economy.\n\nAlvys is positioned at the center of this shift. We are a modern, cloud-native Transportation Management System (TMS) serving carriers and brokers, with growing adoption among larger fleets. As customers move upmarket, the required workflow sophistication increases dramaticallyΓÇöplanning, execution, tracking, compliance, billing, and settlement all need to work together reliably.\n\nAt the same time, the industry is entering an AI-driven transition. The next wave of logistics software will not just record what happened; it will help operators make better decisions in real time by reducing manual work, surfacing the right information, and automating repetitive operational tasks. Our strategy is to build AI into the product where it creates leverage for dispatchers, fleet managers, and operations teamsΓÇöso customers can run faster, with more clarity, and with fewer surprises.\n\nAbout Alvys\n\nAlvys is on a mission to revolutionize transportation logistics. We are evolving from a delivery organization into a product engineering organizationΓÇöone that blends technical excellence with deep product context and financial accountability.\n\nWe measure success by impact, not output. We balance innovation with sustainabilityΓÇöevery feature we build comes with a maintenance cost we own. We think like operators, not just buildersΓÇöreliability and performance are features, not afterthoughts.\n\nEngineering Principles\n\nBuild for Real-World Impact ΓÇö Our users rely on Alvys to solve real problems, not abstract ones.\nExtreme Ownership and Empowerment ΓÇö If itΓÇÖs in production, itΓÇÖs yoursΓÇöquality, uptime, and results.\nTechnology Debt is Strategic, Not Accidental ΓÇö We incur debt deliberately, and pay it down deliberately.\nSimplicity Scales; Complexity Costs ΓÇö We reduce complexity to lower cognitive load and speed up delivery.\nRadical Transparency ΓÇö We share context and data to drive alignment and decision-making.\nEngineering Culture:\n\nMove Fast, Learn Fast ΓÇö Speed is an advantage when paired with good judgment.\nOwn the Outcome ΓÇö We own outcomes end-to-end, not tickets.\nEngineering-Led, Customer-Driven ΓÇö We lead with technical strategy, grounded in customer reality.\nPragmatism Over Purism ΓÇö Maintainability and business impact beat theoretical perfection.\nPeople Over Heroics ΓÇö Sustainability matters; we donΓÇÖt reward burnout.\nTech Stack\nBackend: .NET/C#, CosmosDB, Postgres, Elastic Search, Azure services\nFrontend: TypeScript, React, Angular\nInfrastructure & Ops: Azure, Azure Monitor, Application Insights, CI/CD through DevOps / GitHub Actions\nIntegrations: Multiple third-party APIs and workflow systems\nResponsibilities\nProduct ownership (outcome-driven): Own a product area end-to-end, including problem framing, implementation, rollout, and iteration.\nTechnical leadership: Lead multi-person projects, write and review design docs, and make sound architectural decisions.\nOperational excellence: Build systems that are observable and reliable, participate in incident response, and drive post-incident improvements.\nCross-functional collaboration: Partner closely with Product, Design, and operational stakeholders to ship high-leverage workflow improvements.\nMentorship: Mentor engineers through code reviews, pairing, and setting high standards for quality and product thinking.\nComplexity reduction: Identify opportunities to simplify architecture, workflows, and UX to improve both customer experience and developer velocity.\nMinimum Qualifications\n5+ years of professional software engineering experience, with ownership of production systems.\nStrong proficiency in at least one modern programming language (C#, TypeScript, Java/Kotlin, etc.).\nFull-stack capability: you can contribute across backend services and web UI when needed, and you are comfortable working end-to-end (API ΓåÆ data ΓåÆ UI).\nExperience building and operating production software, including debugging, monitoring/alerting, and performance tuning.\nExperience with data stores in production (relational and/or NoSQL).\nExperience with at least one major cloud provider (Azure, AWS, or GCP).\nStrong collaboration and communication skills with cross-functional partners (Product, Design, and operations stakeholders).\nNote: We care more about demonstrated ability to ship and own outcomes than a specific degree or background.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\nAI-first product engineering experience: you have actively used AI to ship product faster (not just experimentation), and you have refined your personal/team workflow over time.\nChampioning AI adoption: experience introducing AI tooling to a team, setting lightweight standards (prompt/playbook patterns, review practices, safety/quality checks), and helping others level up.\nStrong React proficiency: experience building complex, data-heavy UIs in React and TypeScript, including performance, state management, and maintainable component architecture.\nDesign systems experience: experience building, evolving, or operating within a design system (component libraries, tokens, accessibility, consistency), and partnering effectively with Design.\nExperience building and operating large-scale systems, with a focus on reliability, performance, and cost.\nExperience with observability and operational rigor (dashboards, alerting, incident response, performance tuning).\nExperience with .NET/C#, CosmosDB, Postgres, Elastic Search, and modern web APIs.\nExperience mentoring engineers and raising engineering quality through design reviews, code reviews, and strong technical standards.\nExperience in logistics or transportation software is a plus.\nEqual Employment Opportunity\nAlvys is an equal opportunity employer and as such, we do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws.\n\nWe are dedicated to growing a diverse team of highly talented people. WeΓÇÖre dedicated to building a workplace where we give each other the strategies, support, and space we each need to thriveΓÇöbelieving in and bringing out the best of everyone.\n\nIf you require any accommodations during the recruitment process, whether it be alternate forms of material, accessible meeting rooms, etc., please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.\n\nFor information about Alvys's privacy practices, see our Privacy Policy.	3
