er, you'll shape technical direction, raise the bar for the team, and own outcomes end to end.\nWhat You'll Do\nLead the architecture and development of a world-class billing platform built on Stripe Connect, designed to scale with our growing marketplace\nDesign and implement sophisticated payment flows supporting complex multi-sided marketplace dynamics, including gym owner payouts, member billing, and platform revenue\nOwn financial reporting, reconciliation, and auditability systems that give our business and customers accurate, real-time financial visibility\nDrive compliance across applicable tax, KYC/AML, and regulatory requirements, proactively identifying and addressing risk\nBuild seamless onboarding experiences for gym owners that reduce friction and accelerate time-to-value\nPartner cross-functionally with Product, Finance, and Operations to identify and execute on new monetization opportunities\nMentor engineers on the team, establishing patterns and best practices for building reliable, compliant financial systems\nLead incident response for payment-critical systems and drive improvements that strengthen long-term resilience\nWhat You'll Need\n5+ years of software engineering experience, with 3+ years building and owning production billing or payment systems\nHands-on experience with Stripe Connect or comparable payments platforms (e.g. Square, Adyen, Braintree); Stripe Connect experience strongly preferred\nProven track record designing and scaling billing or payment systems for multi-sided marketplaces\nStrong proficiency in Node.js, TypeScript, React, and REST API design\nDeep understanding of financial systems concepts including subscription billing, revenue recognition, reconciliation, idempotency, and refund flows\nSolid grasp of compliance requirements including PCI DSS, KYC/AML, and tax regulations relevant to payment platforms\nExcellent communication and collaboration skills with the ability to drive alignment across engineering, product, and