at reflect our commitment to healthcare transformation. \n\nLEAD - We innovate to solve problems and believe that everyone can lead by making people and situations better. You'll lead through influence and expertise, innovating solutions that make complex  landscapes more navigable for our teams and clients \n\nDELIVER - We set big goals (Rocks) and focus on making progress every day. You'll drive measurable improvements across the organization whilst maintaining daily focus on systematic progress that enhances our data maturity. \n\nWhat You Will Do: \n\nAs a Software Engineer III ΓÇô Front End, you will design, develop, and deliver scalable software solutions that address complex business challenges. Leveraging your technical expertise, youΓÇÖll architect systems, resolve technical challenges, and implement effective monitoring to ensure system reliability. You will work collaboratively across teams, and adapt solutions for evolving requirements. Your impact will be evident in the quality and efficiency of code delivered, proactive problem resolution, and support of continuous improvement in our engineering processes, directly contributing to the success of your immediate team and projects. \n\nEngineering roles in the Data Solutions Group (DSG) are characterized by the usage of leading-edge cloud-based technologies implemented by self-motivated engineers who collaborate with and are supported by their team at all levels. We set high expectations, but we lift each other up as a team to meet those standards. Team members are engaged with both what is being built and why. A desire to understand our clients, their end-users, and their workflows is part of being on the team. Our clients love our solutions and we are proud to be ranked best in KLAS. \n\nOn the Front-End, we use a flexible, modern architecture using TypeScript with React to build compelling user interfaces and complex functionality. Engineers are empowered and expected to make key decisions in their designs and implementations, supported directly by their leadership. As a senior member on the team, you will also be expected to think and communicate with the team at a high level, while being able to effectively drop into the details, for both your own work and othersΓÇÖ.  \n\nKey Responsibilities: \n\nAdvanced Software Solution Development \n\nImplement clean, maintainable code primarily using Typescript and React, ensuring consistent development practices. \nCollaborate with product managers and cross-functional teams to translate technical specifications into fully functional software features. \nComplex Technical Problem Resolution \n\nDiagnose software and infrastructure issues by applying advanced debugging techniques and analytical thinking. \nIdentify and resolve performance bottlenecks and security vulnerabilities. \nRefine existing processes and code to further improve the teamΓÇÖs throughput and reduce technical debt.  \nDelivery Excellence & Quality Assurance \n\nLeverage true UI tests to cover actual workflows in addition to creating unit tests to ensure software consistency. \nMeet delivery commitments by proactively identifying and addressing obstacles that impact velocity and solution corrrectness.  \nNavigating Ambiguity & Adaptive Delivery \n\nOperate effectively in uncertain environments by designing flexible technical solutions that accommodate evolving requirements. \nModify implementation approaches based on emerging information, balancing depth with agility. \nIterate and validate solutions through continuous testing and feedback, ensuring effectiveness despite ambiguous specifications.  \nExperience You Will Need: \n\n┬╖         8+ years of production JavaScript experience with a deep understanding of TypeScript and its underlying principles. \n\n┬╖         8+ years of production React experience. \n\n┬╖         Experience with a variety of modern React state management libraries, specifically the Flux model and associated libraries. \n\n┬╖  