nd code review triage.\nOwn the Outcome: Drive decisions autonomously within your pod. You balance speed, scalability, and maintainability, with results measured by real-world performance and SLOs.\nMentor the Next Gen: Lead by example and mentor junior engineers on the productive, secure, and high-quality use of AI-assisted development tools.\nGuardian of Trust: Ensure the privacy, security, and performance of AI-generated code, validating every line for correctness before it reaches our members.\nRequirements\n\nExperience: 5ΓÇô8 years of professional full-stack development experience building scalable web applications and microservices.\nAgentic Mastery: 2+ years of hands-on experience using AI coding agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot) in a professional production environment.\nPolyglot Proficiency: Strong proficiency in at least two of the following: TypeScript/JavaScript, Python, or C#/.NET.\nTechnical Depth: Deep experience with modern frontend frameworks (React, Next.js) and a solid understanding of RESTful API design.\nAI Infrastructure: Working knowledge of MCP, Azure AI Foundry, RAG, and LangChain. You understand how to connect LLMs to data.\nCloud & DevOps: Experience architecting on AWS, Azure, or GCP, with a working knowledge of Docker, CI/CD pipelines, and distributed messaging (Redis, Kafka).\nThe Builder's Mindset: Demonstrated ability to evaluate emerging AI tools and a track record of experimenting publicly with new workflows to stay ahead of the curve.\nEducation: BachelorΓÇÖs degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent professional experience.\nBenefits & Perks\n\nExclusive Travel Perks: Access to our private travel marketplace with deeply discounted rates on cruises, resorts, and hotels.\nComprehensive Health: Robust Medical, Dental, and Vision insurance plans.\nFuture Planning: 401(k) with company matching.\nGlobal Connectivity: A remote-friendly or hybrid culture that values "Winning Together" across US and international time zon