echs will be your closest collaborators. You'll help them understand technical issues and turn their escalations into permanent fixes.\nImprove internal tooling. Build and maintain tools around our CI/CD pipeline, GitHub workflows, and deployment processes to make the whole team more efficient.\nWork across a diverse tech stack. On any given week you might be working in C#/.NET on the server side, React/TypeScript on the UI, Rust in the video engine, or Terraform for cloud infrastructure.\n\n\n\nThe Tech Stack:\n\nBackend: C# / .NET, Windows IoT deployment\nFrontend: JavaScript / TypeScript, React, React Router, Remix\nVideo Engine: Rust\nInfrastructure: AWS, Terraform\nTools: GitHub, CI/CD pipelines\n\n\n\nThe Team:\n\nWe're a small, remote, cross-functional team: engineers, a UI/UX developer, support techs, and a training specialist, all working closely together. You'll report to the engineering lead and collaborate most directly with our three support technicians, who are your window into what customers are experiencing day to day.\n\n\n\n\nYou're a Good Fit If You:\n\nYou're comfortable navigating a large, established codebase and enjoy the challenge of understanding how things work before making them better.\nYou can work independently to triage and fix bugs with minimal hand-holding.\nYou're a good communicator who can translate between support/customer language and engineering.\nYou take pride in reliability; you'd rather ship a solid fix than a flashy feature.\nYou're curious enough to jump between C#, TypeScript, Rust, and infrastructure work without getting overwhelmed.\n\n\n\nBonus Points:\n\nExperience with broadcast, video, or multimedia software.\nFamiliarity with Windows IoT or embedded deployment environments.\nBackground in Rust development.\nExperience improving CI/CD pipelines and developer tooling.\nStrong debugging skills across multiple languages and environments.\n\n\n\nDetails:\n\nSalary: $85,000-$95,000 USD (negotiable based on experience)\nLocation: Remote-friendly. The team is based in Minneapolis, MN, with an optional downtown office.\nType: Full-time, exempt\n\n\n\nHow to Apply:\n\nSend us a cover letter and your resume (PDF preferred). In your cover letter, tell us:  \n\nHot take time. In three paragraphs or less, give us your honest opinion on agentic AI. We want to know how (or if) you're using AI in your work, what it's actually good at, and where it lets you down. There's no right answer. We just want to see how you think about tools that are reshaping how we build software.\nTell us a war story. We want to hear about a genuinely difficult bug you tracked down, ideally in a codebase you didn't write. Walk us through the hunt: the wrong turns, the breakthroughs, the moment it finally clicked. We're not looking for a polished interview answer. Details matter.\nDescribe your ideal workday setup. Where are you working? What does your rhythm look like? When do you do your best focused work, and when do you come up for air? We're curious how you structure your day and where you get your energy. Be honest.\n\n\nWe read every cover letter before we look at resumes, so make it count.\n\n\n\n**We'll review all applications within two weeks and let you know if you're invited to continue in the process.	1
