353	Stratford Solutions Inc.	Web Developer	t	2026-03-14 18:23:19.7	Web Developer\nStratford Solutions Inc.\nManhattan, NY ΓÇó Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\n$50 - $55/hr\n\nContractor\n\nPosted 20 hours ago\n\nJob description\nJob Title: Web Developer\n\nLabor Category: Programmer 2\n\nLocation: 100% Remote\n\nJob Type: Contract\n\nWork schedule: Normal business hours, Monday ΓÇô Friday, 35 hours/week (not including mandatory unpaid meal break after 6 hours of work).\n\nDuration: 14 Months (Contract)\n\nPay Rate: $50 - $55 per hour\n\nJob Description / Justification:\n\nThe NYC Civic Engagement Commission is seeking proposals from qualified MWBE-certified vendors for CEC Web Developer (Programmer 2) to upgrade, repair, and support their digital platform, Decidim. This work will directly support The People's Money (CEC's participatory budgeting program) and advance the agency's mission to expand civic participation and engagement across New York City\n\nSCOPE OF SERVICES:\n\nAssisting in upgrading the Ruby on Rails-based platform, Decidim, to the latest version (.31). Updating of the latest version of Decidim will enable us to use the following features:\nTaxonomies - These will give us flexibility in how we display projects and ideas on the website based on categories we create.\nImprove how we sort and filter projects and ideas\nSpam prevention - Currently the CEC spends time manually flagging spam accounts. This feature can save us enormous amounts of time.\nBulk action answers to proposals (what we call ideas) through Answers Templates - This is a huge improvement - it's a feature that would allow us to move ideas from the Idea Generation Phase of The People's Money process in bulk through our process.\nFor example, if we decide that 100 of the ideas are disqualified because they're capital projects, we can select all 100 at once and compose a single message to display: ΓÇ£This idea did not advance to Assemblies because it's a capital projectΓÇ¥ - this helps us t