nhancing platform functionality using Ruby on Rails and other components of the Decidim stack; performing configuration and customization of modules such as Participatory Budgeting, Proposals, and Accountability. The Programmer will also conduct code reviews, troubleshoot issues, resolve bugs, and implement performance improvements to ensure platform reliability, usability, and security.\nAs needed, the Programmer may also support deployment and DevOps processesΓÇösuch as managing environments, CI/CD workflows, and cloud hostingΓÇöto maintain stable and secure platform operation.\nMANDATORY SKILLS/EXPERIENCE\n\nNote: Candidates who do not have mandatory skills will not be considered.\n\nAt least four years of experience with Ruby on Rails.\nAbility to onboard quickly to new platforms and systems, balancing independence with seeking support.\nMinimum four years of experience with version control.\nMinimum four years of experience in front-end web development including JavaScript and CSS.\nMinimum four years of experience working closely with other developers, project managers, and/or designers on a team.\nCandidate's resume MUST include a link to portfolio.\n\nDESIRABLE SKILLS/EXPERIENCE:\n\nExperience working in an agile, iterative development setting.\nExperience working in AWS.	1
