359	Vibility	Full Stack Developer	t	2026-03-14 18:34:19.552	Full Stack Developer\nFreedom Practice Coaching\nSan Antonio, TX ΓÇó Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\n$120K - $140K/yr\n\nFull-time\n\nMedical, Dental, Vision, PTO\n\nPosted 2 days ago\n\nBe Seen First\n\nAfter you apply to this job, you can share why youΓÇÖre interested to jump to the top of the candidate list.\n\nJob description\nAbout Vibility\n\nVibility is building the future of functional medicine delivery. Our platform helps practitioners transform patient care by combining digital health curriculum, accountability tools, outcome tracking, and fractional coaching support into one seamless experience. We exist to make the practitionerΓÇôpatient relationship stronger, more effective, and more scalable.\n\nVibility is part of the Freedom Practice Coaching (FPC) ecosystem, which for over 12 years has empowered 1,000+ wellness practices to grow profitably through training, mentorship, and proven business systems. Together with Aptogenix, a line of professional-grade supplements, this ecosystem equips providers with everything they need to deliver better health outcomes and run thriving practices.\n\nWhile FPC built the playbook for practice growth, Vibility is building the operating system ΓÇö a modern health technology platform that brings education, data, and accountability into the heart of the patient journey. With Vibility, providers can deliver done-for-you curriculum, translate insights from patient feedback into actionable metrics, and leverage fractional health coaches to keep patients supported between visits.\n\n \n\nWho We Serve\n\nIndependent, licensed medical professionals ΓÇö especially in lifestyle, integrative, and functional medicine ΓÇö who operate (or are transitioning to) cash-based practices.\n\n \n\nOur Mission\n\nEmpower wellness providers with the systems, tools, and support to guide their communities toward optimal living ΓÇö helping practitioners grow profitable businesses and create lasting health transformations.\n\nfreedompracticecoaching.com ΓÇó vibility.com ΓÇó aptogenix.com\n\n \n\nThe Role\n\nWeΓÇÖre looking for a Full Stack Developer to join our small, high-output engineering team as we build a modern healthcare platform from the ground up.\n\n \n\nHereΓÇÖs what makes this role different: weΓÇÖre building an AI-first engineering team. YouΓÇÖll use AI tools ΓÇö coding assistants, code generation, automated testing, and more ΓÇö not as a nice-to-have, but as a core part of how you work every day. We believe a small team that deeply leverages AI can move faster and build better software than teams three times its size. If that excites you, keep reading.\n\nYouΓÇÖll work alongside our Senior Full Stack Developer, who leads the platformΓÇÖs technical architecture, to ship features across the entire stack ΓÇö from patient-facing mobile experiences to practitioner dashboards to backend services that power curriculum delivery, progress tracking, and integrations. This is a greenfield build on a modern stack, and youΓÇÖll touch every part of it.\n\nThis isnΓÇÖt a simple CRUD app.\n\n \n\nYouΓÇÖll be working on a multi-tenant, HIPAA-compliant healthcare platform with real architectural depth: serverless APIs with connection pooling, adaptive bitrate video streaming through CloudFront and MediaConvert, async job processing, infrastructure defined as code with AWS CDK, and integrations spanning labs, payments, supplements, and CRM. If youΓÇÖve been looking for a project with genuine technical complexity ΓÇö not just another dashboard ΓÇö this is it.\n\nYou wonΓÇÖt just write code. YouΓÇÖll help design the digital curriculum and accountability framework that lets practitioners extend their care beyond the clinic walls ΓÇö from structured learning journeys to progress tracking to integrations with labs, supplements, and payments. Your work will directly improve real-world health outcomes for thousands of patients.\n\n \n\nWhy This Role Matters\n\nFunctional medicine is more than appointments and lab results. ItΓÇÖs about equipping patients with the education, accountability, and ongoing support they need to change their health long-term. Right now, practitioners lack a cohesive way to deliver that journey ΓÇö theyΓÇÖre forced to cobble together tools that were never designed for this purpose.\n\nWeΓÇÖve built the first version of this solution and are now rebuilding it as a modern, scalable platform. YouΓÇÖll help ship the features that make this platform real ΓÇö building systems for curriculum delivery, patient engagement, and progress tracking that will shape how functional medicine is practiced at scale.\n\n \n\nWhat YouΓÇÖll Do\n\nShip Features Across the Full Stack\n\nBuild and deliver production-ready features across our React front end, Node.js/TypeScript backend, and PostgreSQL database.\nOwn features end-to-end: from understanding the problem, to implementation, to deployment and monitoring.\nWork across patient-facing experiences, practitioner tools, coaching dashboards, and admin systems.\nWork with AWS CDK (TypeScript) to define and evolve infrastructure alongside application code ΓÇö infrastructure is a first-class part of the codebase, not a separate concern.\n \n\nBuild with AI as a Force Multiplier\n\nUse AI coding tools (Cursor, Claude, Copilot, etc.) as a daily part of your development workflow.\nHelp establish and refine AI-assisted development practices across the team ΓÇö prompt engineering, code review of AI output, and knowing when AI accelerates vs. when it doesnΓÇÖt.\nContribute to building internal tools and automations that increase the teamΓÇÖs velocity.\n \n\nCollaborate and Deliver\n\nPartner with the Senior Developer on architecture decisions, code reviews, and technical tradeoffs.\nWork closely with product leadership to translate business requirements into well-scoped technical work.\nCollaborate with specialized contractors (design, DevOps) to maintain momentum.\nContribute to CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, and monitoring for stable, continuous delivery.\n \n\nDesign Systems That Matter\n\nHelp build systems for curriculum delivery, patient engagement tracking, and progress monitoring.\nImplement integrations with labs, supplements, CRM, and payment platforms.\nEnsure HIPAA compliance and secure multi-tenant architecture across everything you build.\n \n\nWhat WeΓÇÖre Looking For\n\nMust-Have\n\n4+ years of full stack development with ownership of production applications. YouΓÇÖve worked on systems with real architectural considerations like async processing, multi-tenancy, third-party integrations, or complex data models.\nStrong React skills ΓÇö you can build responsive, accessible, performant front-end experiences.\nBack-end experience with Node.js/TypeScript and relational databases (PostgreSQL preferred).\nComfortable with cloud infrastructure ΓÇö youΓÇÖve deployed to AWS (or similar) and arenΓÇÖt intimidated by infrastructure-as-code, serverless architectures, or working with services like S3, SQS, and CloudFront.\nActive user of AI development tools ΓÇö you already use AI to write, review, debug, or test code, and youΓÇÖre excited to push that further.\nShipping mindset ΓÇö you care about getting features into usersΓÇÖ hands, not just writing elegant code.\nStartup-ready ΓÇö resourceful, comfortable with ambiguity, fast-moving, and low-ego.\nStrong communication ΓÇö you can work across product, design, and leadership without needing everything spelled out.\n \n\nNice-to-Have\n\nExperience with AWS services (Lambda, RDS, SQS, EventBridge, Cognito).\nPrior work with mobile-first or responsive web applications.\nFamiliarity with healthcare, HIPAA, or regulated industries.\nExperience with infrastructure-as-code (AWS CDK, Terraform, CloudFormation, or Pulumi).\nExperience with Vite, Vercel, Fastify, or similar modern tooling.\nExperience working on multi-tenant SaaS platforms.\nExposure to media pipelines (video transcoding, CDN delivery, streaming).\n \n\nOur Tech Stack\n\nFront End: Vite + React, deployed on Vercel\nBack End: Fastify / Node.js / TypeScript on AWS Lambda, API Gateway\nDatabase: PostgreSQL on AWS RDS with RDS Proxy\nAuth: AWS Cognito\nStorage & CDN: S3, CloudFront (signed URLs, HLS video streaming)\nMedia Processing: AWS MediaConvert (adaptive bitrate transcoding)\nAsync & Scheduling: SQS + EventBridge\nInfrastructure: AWS CDK (TypeScript), Secrets Manager\nAI Tools: Cursor, Claude, and evolving ΓÇö we adopt what works\n \n\nCompensation & Benefits\n\nBase Salary: $135k+, based on experience and skill set\n\nBonus: Performance-based bonuses above base salary\n\nBenefits\n\nFully remote work flexibility\nUnlimited PTO\nPartial health insurance coverage\nProfessional development and mentorship within the FPC ecosystem\nMission-driven culture focused on empowerment, ownership, and continuous improvement\n \n\nTo Apply, please complete this form: https://form.typeform.com/to/vgxO6Xho\n\nCompany Description\nWho is FPC?\nThe Most Comprehensive Healthpreneur Training & Mentorship Program in Existence\nFPC is an ecosystem of health entrepreneurs and business mentors who have built and grown multiple 7-and 8-figure companies.\n\nOver the past 14 years, weΓÇÖve synthesized the most effective models, systems, and tools to help 800+ medical and wellness practices scale profitably. We have built two additional companies to serve the same client population.\nVibility - Health technology, consumer health courses & fractional health coaching\nAptogenix - Professional grade supplements\n\nOur Mission: Empowering our Clients - through business training and personal growth mentoring - to become leading wellness entrepreneurs - who guide their communities toward optimal living.\n\nWebsite - https://freedompracticecoaching.com/\nWebsite - https://vibility.com/\nWebsite - https://aptogenix.com/\n\nReport\n\n	1
